Package homework2

Class Graph<N>

java.lang.Object
homework2.Graph<N>
public class Graph<N>
extends java.lang.Object
A Graph is a mutable model which represents a set of points and the connections between them. A Graph contains a number of nodes {V}, some of which may be connected by edges {E}. Each edge e = (v1,v2) has a direction, which means that the edge (v1,v2) is different from the edge (v2, v1). A Graph cannot have more than one edge which connects a specific node to another. Each node in a Graph can have multiple children and parents. A child of node v is a node u such that there is an edge FROM v to u. In other words, node u is a child of node v if there exists an edge e such that e = (v, u). A parent of node v is a node u such that there is an edge from u to v. In other words, node u is a parent of node v if there exists an edge e such that e = (u, v).

      public void addNode​(N node) throws GraphExceptions.NodeAlreadyExistsException

      Throws:
      GraphExceptions.NodeAlreadyExistsException - if Graph already contains node (or any node with same hash code).

    • addEdge

      public void addEdge​(N parentNode, N childNode) throws GraphExceptions.NodeDoesNotExistException, GraphExceptions.EdgeAlreadyExistsException
      Adds an edge to the Graph.
      Throws:
      GraphExceptions.NodeDoesNotExistException - if Graph does not contain parentNode or childNode or both.
      GraphExceptions.EdgeAlreadyExistsException - if Graph already contains the edge connecting parentNode to childNode.
